1. **Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

The main image shows two structures built from various blocks.  The structure on the left consists of red blocks, forming a small arch-like structure and a small tower. The structure on the right is a tall, central vertical post with a square-ish, multi-layered platform built on top of it. There are several horizontal blocks forming the layers of the upper part of this structure.  There are a total of at least 12 blocks visible; the precise count depends on what is behind other blocks in the structures.  The structures have multiple layers.  The spatial relationships are defined by the relative positions and arrangements of the blocks in each structure.
